269
00:20:10,890 --> 00:20:12,540
Woohyun, do you want to learn as well?

270
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:14,630
I can probably do it with my feet and still be better than her.

271
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:18,100
I can probably own this store just by doing what I've learned by watching over the years.

272
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:21,090
So you can do it? You should have told me earlier.

273
00:20:35,950 --> 00:20:37,490
I put the store up for sale.

274
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:39,630
You put the store for sale?!

275
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,640
I'm getting older.

276
00:20:43,490 --> 00:20:45,550
I want to go on vacation and live in peace.

277
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,070
Ms. Gong,

278
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,670
are you having an affair?

279
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,840
Are you hurt somewhere?

280
00:20:51,110 --> 00:20:53,980
Hurt? I'm still healthy!

281
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:59,470
A few years ago, I was thinking of retiring.

282
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:02,730
But luckily, there was someone who was willing to buy.

283
00:21:03,210 --> 00:21:04,300
Good thinking.

284
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:05,710
I agree.

285
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:09,340
I won't hear your tired sleep talking anymore.

286
00:21:11,970 --> 00:21:13,500
Then, what are we going to eat from now on?

287
00:21:14,430 --> 00:21:15,140
Ms. Gong,

288
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:16,990
do you have a post-retirement plan?

289
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:25,560
This is your school fee,

290
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,660
and this is your wedding money,

291
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:33,080
and this is for your apartment.

292
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:35,100
That's it.

293
00:21:35,310 --> 00:21:37,160
I always prepared it.

294
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:39,110
Why are you being so strange?

295
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:41,120
Are you showing off your money?

296
00:21:41,420 --> 00:21:43,380
I don't want an apartment.

297
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,550
I want to live here with you.

298
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:48,480
This is what you have to decide with your future wife.

299
00:21:49,890 --> 00:21:52,440
Just look carefully!

300
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,360
Fine. There's nothing to see.

301
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:00,800
Since you're always causing trouble,

302
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:03,140
you should grow up now.

303
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:06,050
I'm giving you this so you can take care of yourself.

304
00:22:06,890 --> 00:22:10,020
You need to learn how to look over your own money.

305
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,400
This is too rough.

306
00:22:12,910 --> 00:22:14,690
Up to here, it's rejection.

307
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,540
Grandma was rich...

308
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:21,650
I wasn't rich but I don't want to be regretful.

309
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:25,370
I learned that as I worked hard,

310
00:22:25,370 --> 00:22:28,980
money slowly began to save up and so I can help others.

311
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:31,330
You can live like that, too. Right?

312
00:22:31,630 --> 00:22:33,410
Why are you so strange, Ms. Gong?

313
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:35,210
Grandmother, are you going anywhere?

314
00:22:35,740 --> 00:22:37,310
Go where?

315
00:22:37,420 --> 00:22:39,940
I told you I'm going to go on vacations from now on!

316
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:42,410
But if you go alone, I'm going to get upset.

317
00:22:42,930 --> 00:22:44,990
Let's go on a picnic!

318
00:22:47,260 --> 00:22:49,290
With couple t-shirts!

319
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,500
I have lost the road.

320
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:02,370
My children and myself.

321
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:05,000
Teacher, we all grew up like that.

322
00:23:05,290 --> 00:23:07,270
Recently, the students have only expressed how they feel.

323
00:23:07,740 --> 00:23:11,070
The nature of the stronger one taking advantage of the weaker one has existed from the beginning of time.

324
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,610
Survival of the fittest.

325
00:23:12,820 --> 00:23:15,250
Also, they are of a higher status than us.

326
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:17,560
Higher status than a teacher's status.

327
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:20,090
Teacher, have you known about this?

328
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:23,950
For me, it was so obvious.

329
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:28,140
Only I didn't know

330
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:31,390
how much pain our students were in.

331
00:23:31,870 --> 00:23:34,450
Ah, why are you suddenly blaming yourself?

332
00:23:37,230 --> 00:23:38,710
You should have told me!

333
00:23:39,170 --> 00:23:41,030
I trusted my students!

334
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:45,240
You only saw what you wanted to see and believed what you wanted to believe.

335
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:51,540
Waiting for students who have no judgmental skills is not believing but merely watching in ignorance.

336
00:23:53,670 --> 00:23:55,550
That's my thinking, Teacher.

337
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,160
What should I do?

338
00:24:01,390 --> 00:24:02,690
What could you do?

339
00:24:03,010 --> 00:24:05,060
You have to finish it well.

340
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,900
Before the situation gets worse.

341
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,300
Water?

342
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:35,620
Why do you keep getting involved with Woohyun?

343
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,530
Because he's my friend.

344
00:25:06,990 --> 00:25:10,460
 I still have a long way to go before making up my debt.

345
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,220
I did it because I like you,

346
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:16,250
but for you, I gave you a debt.

347
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:36,460
You want to throw this away?

348
00:25:36,470 --> 00:25:39,220
Yeah, why? Do I have to get permission to throw my clothes away?

349
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:41,220
This is the prettiest though.

350
00:25:41,850 --> 00:25:43,360
If you throw everything away, what are you going to wear?

351
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:45,660
Due to the clothes, the house may explode.

352
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,180
Let me organize while I have the chance.

353
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,000
How many clothes do you think you have, Grandma?

354
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:50,610
Not this either.

355
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:53,440
Give me that! It's old, I need to throw it away!

356
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:58,530
It smells like you, Ms. Gong.

357
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,200
What? It smells like me?

358
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:07,570
A suspicious smell is coming out of it.

359
00:26:08,170 --> 00:26:10,270
If you tell me now, I'll forgive you.

360
00:26:11,230 --> 00:26:12,770
There's no such thing as that kind of a smell.

361
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:15,160
Stop it, my appetite is gone.

362
00:26:20,940 --> 00:26:25,220
Our Ms. Gong's smell. Grandma,

363
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:29,460
if I pay up for all this time I've hurt you, you have to totally live longer.

364
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:32,450
Oh you, you.

365
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:35,580
You smell like sweat! Go shower!

366
00:26:38,610 --> 00:26:39,940
I don't smell.

367
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:43,860
Well, just a little.

368
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,500
What are you doing?

369
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,970
Organizing my clothes.

370
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:03,990
How many clothes do you have to organize as well?

371
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:13,800
Here.

372
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:18,110
Ms. Gong's ddeokbokki recipe.

373
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:20,450
I wrote it down just in case I forgot.

374
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,080
Thank you.

375
00:27:23,670 --> 00:27:25,040
Seulbi,

376
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:29,540
you have to cook while you think of the eater for it to taste well.

377
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:31,570
That's my secret.

378
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:48,200
It would be so good if time stopped like this.

379
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,360
Ms. Gong, are you all ready?

380
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:54,310
Yes, Woohyun, I'm ready.

381
00:27:54,310 --> 00:27:56,560
Did we get everything? Nothing's missing?

382
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:59,030
You only need to pack your senses.

383
00:27:59,030 --> 00:28:01,050
Let's go!

384
00:28:20,150 --> 00:28:22,040
Ms. Gong, get on.

385
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:24,550
It's okay. It makes my butt hurt.

386
00:28:30,750 --> 00:28:32,030
Just wait a little more.

387
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:35,360
I'll earn money soon and let you ride in a convertible.

388
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:36,650
Really?

389
00:28:36,650 --> 00:28:41,590
When I get my paycheck, I'm going to give it all to you. And when I get a car, I'll let you ride in it.

390
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:43,150
Is that right?

391
00:28:43,150 --> 00:28:45,020
Oh, that's good then.

392
00:28:45,020 --> 00:28:47,560
What's this? A doubtful look.

393
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:48,980
Why? Does it hurt you?

394
00:28:48,980 --> 00:28:51,100
As if!

395
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:53,380
Is a convertible really expensive?

396
00:28:53,380 --> 00:28:56,240
Then I'll just get a car with a roof.

397
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:58,120
Is that really possible?

398
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:00,520
Woohyun is similar to Grandma, in that he's being suspicious.

399
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:01,640
Hey!

400
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:04,160
Was Woohyun suspicious of you?

401
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:08,320
Yes, last time, Woohyun—

402
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:10,120
Try and catch me!

403
00:29:11,150 --> 00:29:14,840
If I catch you, you're going to get into a lot of trouble. I'm really fast.

404
00:29:42,490 --> 00:29:46,310
 Woohyun!  Woohyun!  WOOHYUN!

405
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,110
Why is my grandma like that? Why?

406
00:30:07,110 --> 00:30:08,780
Is there no other adult with you?

407
00:30:08,780 --> 00:30:12,560
Please tell me. I'm my grandmother's guardian.

408
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:17,410
By the time she came to the hospital, the gallbladder cancer had already reached its final stage.

409
00:30:17,410 --> 00:30:20,330
It had already spread to the other organs,

410
00:30:20,330 --> 00:30:23,790
so it was too late for treatment.

411
00:30:23,790 --> 00:30:27,300
From now on, you should prepare.

412
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:29,210
Prepare for what?

413
00:30:29,210 --> 00:30:30,770
What should I prepare for?

414
00:30:30,770 --> 00:30:32,580
Woohyun!

415
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:36,030
Save her!  Please, save her!

416
00:30:36,030 --> 00:30:38,380
Please save my grandma!

417
00:30:38,380 --> 00:30:40,240
Please...

418
00:31:16,770 --> 00:31:18,910
You were strange.

419
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:24,170
Ms. Gong, recently you were acting strange. Only I didn't know.

420
00:31:26,450 --> 00:31:31,880
If you're hurt, you should have told me that you're hurt. Why didn't you let me do anything? Why?!

421
00:31:41,730 --> 00:31:43,620
Grandma,

422
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:44,920
are you okay?

423
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:47,840
I'm not okay.

424
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:51,380
You're too noisy.

425
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:54,690
Why didn't you tell me?

426
00:31:54,690 --> 00:31:57,790
It'll hurt me.

427
00:31:58,540 --> 00:32:01,410
I don't like our Woohyun's heart being hurt.

428
00:32:01,410 --> 00:32:04,270
Who says those kinds of things?

429
00:32:04,270 --> 00:32:09,260
I'm Grandma's guardian.  I should know.

430
00:32:10,370 --> 00:32:13,430
Grandma, they'll save you.

431
00:32:13,430 --> 00:32:16,010
So don't worry, okay?

432
00:32:16,010 --> 00:32:18,600
I'm not going to die.

433
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:23,660
Don't worry and take Seulbi back home.

434
00:32:23,660 --> 00:32:27,060
Grandma's scent is not good.

435
00:32:27,060 --> 00:32:28,900
Seulbi,

436
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:31,240
take Woohyun and go home.

437
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:35,070
No, I'm going to stay next to you.

438
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:38,960
Then...

439
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:42,850
can you bring my bag?

440
00:32:42,850 --> 00:32:47,170
Don't forget to lock the doors.

441
00:32:48,170 --> 00:32:50,390
I won't be gone long.

442
00:32:50,390 --> 00:32:52,930
I'm leaving her with you.

443
00:32:58,540 --> 00:33:00,740
Seulbi,

444
00:33:00,740 --> 00:33:05,020
don't you know that you look the prettiest when you smile?

445
00:33:06,340 --> 00:33:08,830
At least, you

446
00:33:08,830 --> 00:33:12,430
smile for me.

447
00:33:12,430 --> 00:33:14,900
Do you understand?

448
00:33:29,770 --> 00:33:32,030
I'm going to sleep.

449
00:33:46,340 --> 00:33:48,600
How could this...

450
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:33,860
Ms. Gong...

451
00:34:33,860 --> 00:34:35,540
You're lying, right?

452
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:37,480
Get up right now.

453
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,960
I thought you said you couldn't live if you didn't see me.

454
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:42,010
I couldn't do anything for Grandma!

455
00:34:42,010 --> 00:34:45,110
What do you expect me to do by myself?

456
00:34:45,110 --> 00:34:47,870
I can't live either if I don't have you.

457
00:34:47,870 --> 00:34:49,550
Get up, please!

458
00:34:49,550 --> 00:34:51,600
Get up!

459
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:53,580
Grandma...

460
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:58,380
Grandma, get up.

461
00:34:58,380 --> 00:35:01,760
Save her... Save her...

462
00:35:06,590 --> 00:35:09,010
 - Grandma...  
 - Senior!

463
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:14,230
Nothing will change just because you're doing this.

464
00:35:14,230 --> 00:35:16,550
Wait.

465
00:35:16,550 --> 00:35:19,440
Take Grandma a bit later.

466
00:35:19,440 --> 00:35:20,900
I beg  of you.

467
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:23,790
Seulbi,

468
00:35:23,790 --> 00:35:26,280
you can see me?

469
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:31,830
Are you an angel?

470
00:35:31,830 --> 00:35:34,550
Grandma...

471
00:35:34,550 --> 00:35:37,530
We can't change a person's fate.

472
00:35:37,530 --> 00:35:41,430
Humans will always die,

473
00:35:41,430 --> 00:35:45,360
that the death of a person is definite,

474
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:50,360
that's why now I'm receiving the punishment.

475
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:55,980
If I knew how much the heart hurts like this,

476
00:35:55,980 --> 00:35:58,250
if so,

477
00:35:59,110 --> 00:36:03,220
I would have been kinder when talking to a dead person.

478
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:09,180
At least let them say goodbye to their loved ones.

479
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:14,720
When they asked how the people they left behind are doing,

480
00:36:16,250 --> 00:36:19,160
I should have kindly told them.

481
00:36:21,780 --> 00:36:24,350
Senior,

482
00:36:24,350 --> 00:36:26,610
I beg you.

483
00:36:34,730 --> 00:36:38,230
My poor Puppy.

484
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:41,250
Grandma is really sorry.

485
00:36:48,630 --> 00:36:50,560
Let's go.

486
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:16,060
If I'm not here, Woohyun will be all alone.

487
00:37:16,100 --> 00:37:18,800
How do I tell him that I'm leaving?

488
00:37:21,900 --> 00:37:24,200
You're leaving?

489
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,700
Woohyun...

490
00:37:28,740 --> 00:37:31,370
About that...

491
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:34,100
I have to go back now.

492
00:37:36,170 --> 00:37:39,660
Your memory returned?

493
00:37:39,660 --> 00:37:41,760
Yeah...

494
00:37:44,020 --> 00:37:46,910
When are you leaving?

495
00:37:46,910 --> 00:37:52,330
I couldn't tell you before. I'm sorry.

496
00:37:52,330 --> 00:37:55,240
You did great, so go.

497
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:57,120
Woohyun...

498
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:59,100
Go.

499
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:01,200
Just go!

500
00:38:03,450 --> 00:38:05,870
Woohyun!

501
00:38:09,690 --> 00:38:16,560
♫  That’s not how I feel, I’ve never hated you  ♫

502
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:21,270
♫  I hope our love will never change  ♫

503
00:38:21,270 --> 00:38:27,970
♫  I hope we will always smile  ♫

504
00:38:27,970 --> 00:38:30,810
♫  Thank you  ♫

