Who is? Mom?

538
00:41:31,490 --> 00:41:35,210
 I really want a "congrats" from you.

539
00:41:35,210 --> 00:41:39,640
 You're grown up now and I feel that you'll understand me.

540
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:45,160
I still have time to grow up. And even if I become an adult, I'll never understand you and Dad.

541
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,760
 Is it okay if you're happy?

542
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:51,050
Me! What about me!?

543
00:41:51,050 --> 00:41:53,460
Why doesn't anyone care?

544
00:41:53,460 --> 00:41:55,100
If you're going to abandon me, why did you give birth to me?!

545
00:41:55,100 --> 00:41:57,170
 Sungyeol. Hwang Sungyeol.

546
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:18,740

547
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:27,900
 Adults are very bad.

548
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:36,600
 It's not because they don't like you that they leave.

549
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:39,710
 They thought you would understand.

550
00:42:40,930 --> 00:42:43,480
 Since you're their son.

551
00:42:48,110 --> 00:42:50,660
 Anyway, it's nice.

552
00:43:06,100 --> 00:43:09,380
Did you meet someone at the funeral?

553
00:43:09,380 --> 00:43:11,750
Oh, no.

554
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:14,300
She must have got the wrong person.

555
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:18,200
Woohyun and Sungyeol, I think they're good friends.

556
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:21,600
Those rascals.

557
00:43:25,110 --> 00:43:28,730
What will happen to Woohyun? His father is all the way in the US.

558
00:43:28,730 --> 00:43:31,410
Is there no way of contacting him?

559
00:43:31,410 --> 00:43:35,480
What about his mother? Should I look for her?

560
00:43:35,480 --> 00:43:37,170
Why?

561
00:43:37,170 --> 00:43:39,340
Why would you?

562
00:43:39,340 --> 00:43:42,460
The kids may end up just getting hurt.

563
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:46,600
Plus, he's probably having a hard time right now.

564
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:48,360
Is that so?

565
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:52,640
Well, you did major in that area.

566
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:55,850
Oh! I'm tired.

567
00:44:09,010 --> 00:44:12,790
I didn't even know that Grandma was sick.

568
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:16,500
I asked her if she had a boyfriend.

569
00:44:16,590 --> 00:44:18,480
How funny.

570
00:44:21,450 --> 00:44:25,020
Grandma only scolded.

571
00:44:25,100 --> 00:44:30,300
I'm sorry for leaving you alone like this.

572
00:44:30,300 --> 00:44:35,700
I purposely had fits and caused trouble.

573
00:44:37,530 --> 00:44:40,040
I'm a bastard.

574
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:44,580
Do you know how happy I was because of you?

575
00:44:44,580 --> 00:44:47,730
You miss your parents, so what should you do?

576
00:44:47,730 --> 00:44:51,570
What do you do since you miss them?

577
00:44:51,570 --> 00:44:56,420
What should I do when I miss you and want to touch you?

578
00:44:56,500 --> 00:45:02,100
Even though you took all those medicines like your meals, I didn't know.

579
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:06,910
I just...

580
00:45:06,910 --> 00:45:10,180
I just thought that you'd always live with me.

581
00:45:13,890 --> 00:45:16,570
I thought you wouldn't die.

582
00:45:16,570 --> 00:45:18,620
It hurts Woohyun!

583
00:45:18,700 --> 00:45:22,400
Don't say that! It's not your fault.

584
00:45:29,650 --> 00:45:33,520
What can I do about you guys?

585
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:07,710
I should have given this to you earlier, but I didn't have time.

586
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:12,010
You looked like you enjoyed listening to music.

587
00:46:13,570 --> 00:46:15,610
You're weird today.

588
00:46:16,590 --> 00:46:19,950
If you press this and make a wish, that wish will come true.

589
00:46:19,970 --> 00:46:21,450
I collect these as well.

590
00:46:21,450 --> 00:46:24,280
Really? As expected, we understood each other.

591
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:25,890
Understood?

592
00:46:25,890 --> 00:46:27,790
Why is it past tense?

593
00:46:29,670 --> 00:46:31,980
Thank you...

594
00:46:32,030 --> 00:46:33,740
I have to go back.

595
00:46:33,740 --> 00:46:35,770
To where?

596
00:46:35,770 --> 00:46:38,150
It's a place you don't know of.

597
00:46:42,190 --> 00:46:44,580
I was always thankful.

598
00:46:46,850 --> 00:46:49,020
If I don't accept this,

599
00:46:49,020 --> 00:46:50,690
will you not go?

600
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:58,240
For being my friend,

601
00:46:58,240 --> 00:47:00,100
I was glad.

602
00:47:01,900 --> 00:47:04,160
I'll miss you.

603
00:47:13,570 --> 00:47:15,940
You're good at everything, so...

604
00:47:24,860 --> 00:47:27,750
I really don't know why

605
00:47:28,910 --> 00:47:30,940
you're saying goodbye.

606
00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:14,380
Woohyun...

607
00:48:16,070 --> 00:48:17,920
Now, I have to...

608
00:48:20,350 --> 00:48:22,090
You haven't left?

609
00:48:23,810 --> 00:48:25,360
Go.

610
00:48:26,410 --> 00:48:28,100
I said go!

611
00:48:56,190 --> 00:49:01,760

612
00:49:07,210 --> 00:49:09,020
We should go.

613
00:49:10,450 --> 00:49:14,760
Because of you, Woohyun seems happier.

614
00:49:15,440 --> 00:49:17,880
Let's leave him alone and go.

615
00:49:19,850 --> 00:49:21,600
Grandma...

616
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:25,950
Seulbi, do well.

617
00:49:38,410 --> 00:49:41,690
Go to him and hit him.

618
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:46,310
Just hit him really hard.

619
00:49:46,310 --> 00:49:49,700
I taught My Puppy not to cry.

620
00:49:49,700 --> 00:49:51,840
He can't even cry.

621
00:49:51,860 --> 00:49:55,860
Just hit him so he can cry peacefully.

622
00:49:59,290 --> 00:50:04,950
Seulbi, I'm leaving Woohyun with you.

623
00:50:07,400 --> 00:50:12,110
You're so pretty when you smile.

624
00:50:13,850 --> 00:50:15,960
We should go now.

625
00:50:22,030 --> 00:50:25,030
My Puppy...

626
00:50:25,030 --> 00:50:27,040
He's strong.

627
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:43,600
Grandma...

628
00:50:53,160 --> 00:50:54,720
Ms. Gong,

629
00:50:55,470 --> 00:50:57,410
it's nice here.

630
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:01,290
The breeze is nice.

631
00:51:01,350 --> 00:51:03,970
And they say that, in spring, a lot of flowers bloom.

632
00:51:04,940 --> 00:51:08,290
In autumn, there are a lot of colors.

633
00:51:08,290 --> 00:51:10,630
Will it be cold in the winter?

634
00:51:25,710 --> 00:51:27,730
It's time for you to go.

635
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:32,380
- I haven't said goodbye— 
 - Farewells are best when they are short and fast.

636
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:35,250
If you're like this then it's only hard on that guy.

637
00:51:37,430 --> 00:51:41,700
You've sworn to the book. You will have to return for everything to turn back to normal.

638
00:51:41,730 --> 00:51:44,470
You and him.

639
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:47,970
Ms. Gong,

640
00:51:49,400 --> 00:51:52,090
Seulbi left, too.

641
00:51:52,090 --> 00:51:53,930
She was annoying.

642
00:51:55,010 --> 00:51:56,880
It's good.

643
00:51:59,560 --> 00:52:03,040
Let's go.  Quickly, Senior.

644
00:52:09,090 --> 00:52:11,620
Do well, Woohyun.

645
00:52:18,250 --> 00:52:20,060
Now, I'm...

646
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:24,350
really alone.

647
00:52:27,220 --> 00:52:28,760
Grandma...

648
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:31,930
I'm sorry.

649
00:52:31,930 --> 00:52:35,110
I only think of the bad things I have done.

650
00:52:38,390 --> 00:52:40,890
How do I live now?

651
00:52:44,500 --> 00:52:50,480

652
00:53:02,620 --> 00:53:04,190
 Did I really become human!?

653
00:53:04,190 --> 00:53:07,550
 Why do humans love when they know they're going to separate?

654
00:53:07,590 --> 00:53:09,890
 Why do you live when you know you're going to die?

655
00:53:09,940 --> 00:53:13,760
 What it feels like to be hurt or what it feels like to be happy.

656
00:53:15,540 --> 00:53:18,260
 What it feels like to be in love.

657
00:53:19,730 --> 00:53:22,130
 Lee Seulbi, come over to me now.

658
00:53:22,150 --> 00:53:23,840
 That's a relief.

659
00:53:23,890 --> 00:53:28,380
 After I became a human, the first person I met was you.
